description: Garvin Bushell interviewed by Joe Williams on the program "Jump For Jazz." Garvin Bushell talks about early jazz and recording with Bunk Johnson in 1947. A musical example of "The Entertainer", a recording by Bunk Johnson's band made in 1947 in New York City with Garvin Bushell on clarinet is included.
creator: Buck Johnson New Orleans Band
